<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Tsoakae (29) told Daily Sun the vegetable robbers terrorised him for more than two years and he didn’t know what to do.“I had a passion for planting vegetables because I used to get piece jobs on farms where we used tractors to plough and plant,” he said. “I decided to use my backyard and started to plant.”But when he was ready to enjoy the fruits of his hard work, thugs stole all his vegetables. “I was deeply hurt and that’s when I decided to speak to my ancestors,” Tsoakae told the People’s Paper.“The ancestors came to me in a dream.“They told me to go to a nearby dam and I would find an old tree and a wheelbarrow.“They told me to place them near my door and to always keep the area clean.“After I getting the tree, I found old shells that I was told to also put in front of my doors.“Ever since then I’ve had the best sleep ever.“Thugs don’t terrorise me anymore and my vegetable garden is safe.”He said he was grateful to his ancestors for coming to his rescue.“I am happy that the ancestors are protecting me. “Now I’m able to enjoy the vegetables from my garden.”